column4: How can I get my processor type (32/64 bit) from ubuntu?
you can find if you're running 32 or 64 by doing "uname -a"
and i686 is what kind? I don't see the number 32 or 64 there :D
that gives no output -- what line in there should I be looking at?
do you know which cpu you have? try pastebin'ing "cat /proc/cpuinfo"
not necessarily faster, but it uses the processor more efficiently, how it was designed.
